@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "Konnex" where you
want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files
or Libraries are needed. However, the game requires a 68020(+)
Amiga with Workbench 2.0 or higher.

                             How to play?

  The game is played on a game board of a variable size, but only
a small portion (a display of 5 by 5 tiles) of it can be seen at
all time. To help you find your way in the game area, a small
display, shown at right shows where the 5 by 5 area is located
(indicated by a small square) in the entire game board (which is
indicated by a solid coloured rectangle).

  The game display consists of 2 types of 'zones', each with its
own function, that can be clicked on:

'Center-9' zone: This zone has between 4 and 9 'embossed frame'
                 tiles (depending on where you are located in the
                 game area) at the central part of the display.
                 When you click on one of these tiles, their
                 connections will rotate clockwise by 90 degrees.

'Out-16' zone: This zone has 'normal' tiles, they surround the
               central zone (or 'Center-9'). Clicking on one of
               these tiles will make you move in the game area, and
               the clicked tile will then be located at the center
               of the display.

  The goal is to connect together all the tiles of the game board,
in the least amount of moves. When a game board is completed,
Konnex will generate a new bigger board, up to a maximum size of
19 by 19 tiles.

  You can restart the game anytime, by clicking on the @{b}New Game@{ub}
button.

  Have fun!

  You can quit the game by clicking on the game window's close
button or by pressing on the 'Esc' key.

